{"ts": "2026-05-05T19:53:59Z", "event": "clarify_critic", "feature": "fix-archive-predicate-and-sweep-lifecycle-and-research-dirs", "parent_epic_loaded": true, "findings": [{"text": "The Intent clarity HIGH rating treats the F-9a regex as a settled specification while the source's same-ticket F-9b table is the only artifact that would empirically validate the regex's coverage; circular dependency between F-9a (regex) and F-9b (validation enumeration) is not flagged.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "The Intent clarity HIGH rating papers over that the central safety-critical decision (Option 1 modify bin/ vs Option 2 sequence-and-accept) is by-design unresolved with materially different scope.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "The Scope boundedness HIGH rating asserts the 4 manually-archived dirs are enumerated, but ~32 of 37 lifecycle dirs have unknown disposition until F-9b's table is produced inside this same ticket \u2014 bound is procedural ('we will produce a table'), not substantive.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "The Scope boundedness HIGH rating treats '~30' counts and 'Sample-classified dirs to archive include...' as bounded, but these are predictions and samples; F-10 explicitly defers full enumeration to Plan.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "The Scope boundedness HIGH rating cites the out-of-scope list but ignores hard temporal couplings: 'Code-reference paired update' on cortex_command/cli.py:268 (a file-state invariant inside #166) and the 'Ordering constraint: sequence #169 last after #166 and #168 commit'.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "The Requirements alignment HIGH rating does not address that under Option 1, modifying bin/cortex-archive-rewrite-paths is a dual-sourced shared utility per CLAUDE.md's 'New global utilities ship via the cortex-core plugin's bin/ directory' and dual-source enforcement convention.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "The Requirements alignment HIGH claim cites 'share-ready state for installer audience' but the parent epic's audience is 'people running cortex init... not forkers' \u2014 installers consuming via 'uv tool install' do not pull lifecycle/ or research/ at all; the alignment may be reading the parent's framing more permissively than stated.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "The complexity=complex and criticality=medium tiers are preset and not challenged; modifying bin/cortex-archive-rewrite-paths is shared agentic-layer tooling per the criticality high definition; the 'Critical:' section header about blast radius affecting alive epic #82's research artifact suggests criticality may be under-rated.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "The Intent clarity HIGH reasoning treats F-9a/F-9b/F-9c/F-10 as clean decomposition, but F-9c's intent is contingent on F-9b's measured output ('~19 strict + ~11 YAML-form once predicate is fixed' are predictions, not measurements) \u2014 sequential-dependent decomposition.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "The acceptance signal 'No load-bearing cross-references broken (verify backlog/029-...md:59 still resolves)' is a single-citation spot-check while the body itself enumerates multiple at-risk live cross-reference sources (research/repo-spring-cleaning/research.md, research/opus-4-7-harness-adaptation/research.md, in-flight #166/#168 lifecycle artifacts, backlog ticket bodies); acceptance signals are under-specified relative to the body's own enumerated risks.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Parent-epic alignment is asserted on the basis of 'share-ready state for installer audience', but the clarified intent's primary deliverables (sweeping lifecycle/ and research/ into archive subdirs) improve forker-facing repo navigability (these are not paths a 'cortex init' consumer interacts with); divergence between child #169's lifecycle/research target surface and parent #165's stated installer audience is unjustified by the source material.", "origin": "alignment"}], "dispositions": {"apply": 7, "dismiss": 3, "ask": 1}, "applied_fixes": ["Revised scope-boundedness reasoning: HIGH retained, but acknowledged that the bulk of in-scope dirs (~32 of 37 lifecycle; all ~30 research) are predicate-determined inside this ticket via F-9b/F-10 tables \u2014 not pre-enumerated. Boundedness rests on the decision rule (regex predicate) being well-specified, not on the dir set being pre-listed.", "Acknowledged ticket counts ('~30') are predictions; measured volumes come from F-9b/F-10 table runs. The decision rule still bounds inclusion deterministically.", "Added precondition note: scope has hard temporal couplings to siblings (#169 sequenced after #166 + #168; cli.py:268 file-state invariant from #166). These are sequencing preconditions not scope ambiguity, but they are preconditions that must be checked before execution.", "Carry research consideration: Option 1 (adding --exclude-dir to bin/cortex-archive-rewrite-paths) must respect the dual-source canonical-and-mirror enforcement convention for cortex-core plugin bin/ utilities.", "Refined requirements-alignment reasoning: the parent epic's installer-audience framing primarily targets 'uv tool install' consumers who do not pull lifecycle/ or research/ at all. #169's sweep primarily improves GitHub-repo-render visible to evaluators/browsers/forkers. Alignment retained but narrower than asserted; this distinction propagates as a research consideration.", "Acknowledged acceptance signals are spot-check style; expanded verification criteria (enumerate at-risk citation sources before the sweep; verify each survives the rewrite-paths recipe) is a Spec-phase deliverable.", "Carry alignment-research consideration: validate that the GitHub-repo-render impact of sweeping lifecycle/ and research/ reaches installer-evaluator visibility (people browsing the repo to evaluate cortex before installing) \u2014 not only forker-facing surface."], "dismissals": [{"finding_index": 0, "rationale": "events.log is line-oriented NDJSON or YAML-block convention per cortex-command lifecycle write paths; pretty-printed JSON spanning lines and inline YAML comments do not occur in practice. The F-9b/F-9a circular dependency is intentional intra-ticket validation (F-9b empirically confirms F-9a's coverage), not a goal ambiguity."}, {"finding_index": 1, "rationale": "The goal 'mitigate cortex-archive-rewrite-paths blast radius' is unambiguous; the technical path is by design a Plan-phase decision with a stated recommendation. Lifecycle separates intent (Clarify) from technical-decision selection (Plan); two clearly-stated mitigation options with a recommendation is the normal Plan-phase setup, not a Clarify-phase ambiguity."}, {"finding_index": 8, "rationale": "Sequential dependencies between sub-deliverables within a single feature lifecycle (F-9b empirically validates F-9a's coverage; F-9c executes from F-9b's table) are a normal decomposition pattern that the lifecycle state machine is designed to handle, not a signal of unclear intent. The decision rule (regex predicate) is well-specified; only the measured set is ticket-internal-pending."}], "status": "ok"}
